Two alleged house robbers escaped from custody at the Parkview police station on Monday in an incident that led to the death of one of the suspects. JOHANNESBURG Police watchdog the Independent Police Investigative Directorate (Ipid) is expected to investigate how two alleged house robbers managed to escape from custody at the Parkview station on Monday in an incident that led to the death of one of the suspects.The pair were arrested on Monday morning but managed to escape, with officers only managing to re-arrest one man.His alleged accomplice ran toward Zoo Lake where he later drowned.The police s Kay Makhubele says: So far the police divers were called, and he was removed. Unfortunately he had already passed on. We are investigating a case of inquest and the matter will also be investigated by the Ipid. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)